=================================================================================================
(Introductory Remarks)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NAME    1: Variables for contouring
LWTI  2-3: Interval of continuous thick Line and putting label on contour line
LWTH    4: Thickness of contour line
INTV    5: Interval of contour lines
BASE    6: Basic reference Value for contour
BMIN    7: Min value for contouring is based BASE(BASE - n*INTV)
BMAX    8: Max value for contouring is based BASE(BASE + n*INTV)
SMBL    9: Max/Min Value Symbol(0:+/-,1:H/L,2:W/C,3:D:M)(ex: High,Low,Warm,Cold,Dry,Moisture)
PTLN   10: Pattern of contour line(1:solid, 0:dash)
CRLN   11: Color of contour line(0:white,1:black,2:red,3:green,4:blue,see subroute make_gscrtbl)
CRMX   12: Color of Max value(0:W,1:Bl,2:R,3:G,4:B,negative(-): no labling(-9),and no plotting)
CRMN   13: Color of Max value(0:W,1:Bl,2:R,3:G,4:B,negative(-): no labling(-9),and no plotting)
=================================================================================================
